Usage: pmrep [option...] metricspec [...]

General options:
  -a FILE, --archive=FILE
                        metrics source is a PCP log archive
  --archive-folio=FILE  read metric source archives from a folio
  --container=NAME      specify an individual container to be queried
  -h HOST, --host=HOST  metrics source is PMCD on host
  -L, --local-PMDA      metrics source is local connection to a PMDA
  -K SPEC, --spec-local=SPEC
                        optional additional PMDA spec for local connection
  -c FILE, --config=FILE
                        config file path
  -C, --check           check config and metrics and exit
  -o OUTPUT, --output=OUTPUT
                        output target: archive, csv, stdout (default), or zabbix
  -F OUTFILE, --output-file=OUTFILE
                        output file
  -e FILE|DFNT, --derived=FILE|DFNT
                        derived metrics definitions
  -V, --version         display version number and exit
  -?, --help            show this usage message and exit

Reporting options:
  -H, --no-header       omit headers
  -U, --no-unit-info    omit unit info from headers
  -G, --no-globals      omit global metrics
  -p, --timestamps      print timestamps
  -A TIME, --align=TIME align sample times on natural boundaries
  -S TIME, --start=TIME start of the time window
  -T TIME, --finish=TIME
                        end of the time window
  -O TIME, --origin=TIME
                        initial sample time within the time window
  -s N, --samples=N     terminate after this many samples
  -t DELTA, --interval=DELTA
                        sampling interval
  -Z TZ, --timezone=TZ  set reporting timezone
  -z, --hostzone        set reporting timezone to local time of metrics source
  -d, --delay           delay, pause between updates for archive replay
  -r, --raw             output raw counter values (no rate conversion)
  -i STR, --instances=STR
                        instances to report (default: all current)
  -X STR, --colxrow=STR swap stdout columns and rows using header label
  -w N, --width=N       default column width
  -P N, --precision=N   N digits after the decimal separator (if width enough)
  -l STR, --delimiter=STR
                        delimiter to separate csv/stdout columns
  -x, --extended-header display extended header
  -E N, --repeat-header=N
                        repeat stdout headers every N lines
  -f STR, --timestamp-format=STR
                        strftime string for timestamp format
  -u, --no-interpol     disable interpolation mode with archives
  -q SCALE, --count-scale=SCALE
                        default count unit
  -b SCALE, --space-scale=SCALE
                        default space unit
  -y SCALE, --time-scale=SCALE
                        default time unit
